Get-Item <file> | Get-Content -Stream Zone.Identifier
Powershell way to ident the zone id in the alternate data stream of a file

################

Get-CimInstance -ClassName Win32OperatingSystem | Select-Object -Property CSName, Caption, Version, BuildNumber, BuildType, OSType, RegisteredUser, OSArchitecture, ServicePackMajorVersion

Get-Service | Where-Object { $.Status -eq "Running" }

gcim - alias for Get-CimInstance

Get-Alias shows all aliases available

A Powershell function, unlike a cmdlet is not pre-compiled in .Net
Functions are stored as local modules

Use ISE to create a custom funcion
Use Import-Module to load it into Powershell
Carrie Roberts class on Powershell

